A woman was taken to hospital suffering from smoke inhalation after being rescued from a blaze at a flat in Glasgow. Woman taken to hospital after Glasgow flat blaze A woman was taken to hospital suffering from smoke inhalation after being rescued from a blaze at a flat in Glasgow. 
Two other people were led to safety from the fire which broke out in a ground-floor flat on Bolton Drive in the south of the city. 
Four Scottish Fire and Rescue Service appliances were sent to tackle the blaze shortly after 12:00.
The fire was put out a short time later and no other injuries were reported.
 